			<ns0:name>s...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108394971971967673680/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">This bug has turned into multiple issues.  So far I have:

1) fixed a wart with the Mac imc_sendmsg implementation that allowed short message reads followed by confusion in IMC (3555002, r3426).

2) enabled passing errno=EMSGSIZE back from imc_sendmsg.  This will allow the SRPC message fragmentation to try backing off from an initial fragment size until finding a successful one (3687005, r3444).

The next fix (3532007) is to enable message fragmentation in SRPC.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2010-10-12T16:17:28.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-10-12T16:17:28.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 5 by s...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=935#c5" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/935/comments/full/5" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>